{"title_page": "Official Opposition frontbench", "text_new": "{{See also|Shadow Cabinet of Keir Starmer}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date = March 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2020}}\n\nThe '''frontbench of Her Majesty's Loyal Opposition''' in the [[Parliament of the United Kingdom]] consists of the [[Official Opposition Shadow Cabinet (United Kingdom)|Shadow Cabinet]] and other official shadow ministers of the political party currently serving as the [[Her Majesty's Most Loyal Opposition (United Kingdom)|Official Opposition]]. Her Majesty's Loyal Opposition is currently the [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]], and the [[Leader of the Opposition (United Kingdom)|Leader of the Opposition]] is [[Keir Starmer]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://labourlist.org/2020/04/shadow-ministers-appointed-as-starmer-completes-frontbench/|title=Shadow ministers appointed as Starmer completes frontbench|last=Rodgers|first=Sienna|date=2020-04-09|website=LabourList|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\n==Key==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| style=\"background: {{House of Commons/meta/color}}; width: 1px;\" |\n| Member of the House of Commons\n|-\n| style=\"background: {{House of Lords/meta/color}}; width: 1px;\" |\n| Member of the House of Lords\n|-\n| style=\"background: {{Privy Council/meta/color}}; width: 1px;\" |\n| [[Privy Council of the United Kingdom|Privy Counsellor]]\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" | Shadow Cabinet full members '''in bold'''\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" | Shadow Cabinet attendees '''in bold italics'''\n|}\n\n==Leader of the Opposition and Shadow Cabinet Office==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! colspan=\"4\" | [[Leader of the Opposition (United Kingdom)|Office of the Leader of the Opposition]]\n|-\n| style=\"background: {{House of Commons/meta/color}}; width: 1px;\" rowspan=\"3\" |\n| style=\"width: 450px;\" | [[Leader of the Opposition (United Kingdom)|Leader of Her Majesty's Most Loyal Opposition]]<br />[[Leader of the Labour Party (UK)|Leader of the Labour Party]]\n| style=\"ba