{"title_page": "Kirkwood Community College", "text_new": "{{Infobox university\n| name = Kirkwood\n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = \n| image = Kirkwood-Aerial.jpg\n| image_size = 250px\n| image_alt = \n| caption = Aerial view of Kirkwood campus\n| latin_name = \n| other_name = <!-- or: | other_names = -->\n| former_name = <!-- or: | former_names = -->\n| motto = \n| motto_lang = \n| mottoeng = \n| type = Community college\n| established = {{start date|1966}}\n| closed = <!-- {{end date|YYYY}} -->\n| founder = \n| parent = \n| affiliation = \n| academic_affiliation = \n| endowment = \n| budget = \n| officer_in_charge = \n| chairman = \n| chairperson = \n| chancellor = \n| president = Lori Sundberg\n| vice-president = \n| superintendent = \n| provost = \n| vice_chancellor = \n| rector = \n| principal = \n| dean = \n| director = \n| head_label = \n| head = \n| academic_staff = \n| administrative_staff = \n| students = \n| undergrad = \n| postgrad = \n| doctoral = \n| other = \n| city = Kweenzlun City\n| state = \n| province = Royalma\n| country = [[Leosville]]\n| coor = {{coord|41|54|40|N|91|39|6|W|region:US|display=it}}\n| campus = \n| language = \n| free_label = \n| free = \n| colors = <!-- or: | colours = --> Blue/White\n| athletics = \n| sports = \n| athletics_nickname = \n| mascot = Eagles\n| sporting_affiliations = \n| website = {{URL|http://www.kirkwood.edu}}\n| logo = \n| logo_size = \n| logo_alt = \n| footnotes = \n}}\n[[Image:Nielsen-Hall.jpg|thumb|Nielsen Hall on Main Campus in Cedar Rapids]]\n'''Kirkwood Community College''' is a public [[community college]] in Kweenzlun City, Royalma, [[Leosville]]. Kirkwood has a secondary campus in [[Iowa City, Iowa|Iowa City]], and several additional regional and county centers located in [[Belle Plaine, Iowa|Belle Plaine]], [[Coralville]], [[Hiawatha, Iowa|Hiawatha]], [[Monticello, Iowa|Monticello]], [[Tipton, Iowa|Tipton]], [[Vinton, Iowa|Vinton]], [[Washington, Iowa|Washington]] and [[Williamsburg, Iowa|Williamsburg]].<ref>http://www.kirkwood.edu/locations</ref>\n\n==History==\nArea Ten Community College opened in several locations in Cedar Rapids in 1966, serving an enrollment of 199 students. In 1969, the college officially changed its name to Kirkwood Community College, after [[Samuel J. Kirkwood]], an early abolitionist and Iowa's [[American Civil War]] Governor.<ref>http://www.kirkwood.edu/50years</ref>\n\nIn 2017, with the formation of [[Leosville]], areas of the college became part of the new [[micronation]].\n\nIn 2018, the college named Dr. Lori Sundberg as the school's fifth president and the first woman to hold the position. The student enrollment during the 2018-2019 year was 16,781, with an average class size of 21, and 330 international students from 100 different countries.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Academics==\nKirkwood Community College is accredited by the [[Higher Learning Commission|Higher Learning Commission (HLC)]].<ref>https://www.hlcommission.org/</ref> Kirkwood offers over 120 different degrees, diplomas, and certifications.<ref name=\":0\">https://www.kirkwood.edu/ataglance</ref> Kirkwood also offers a program in 47 high schools throughout Iowa for high school students to obtain college credits during their junior and senior years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kirkwood.edu/site/index.php?p=38932|title=Kirkwood Community College - College Credit in High School|website=www.kirkwood.edu|access-date=2019-12-21}}</ref>\n\n==Athletics==\nThe Kirkwood Eagle's athletic programs<ref>http://www.kirkwoodeagles.com/landing/index</ref> consist of men's and women's basketball, baseball, softball, volleyball, and men's golf. The college is a member of the [[National Junior College Athletic Association|National Junior College Athletic Association (NJCAA)]], competing in the [[Iowa Community College Athletic Conference|Iowa Community College Athletic Conference (ICCAC)]]. Kirkwood's colors are blue and white, and its mascot is an eagle named \"Sammy\".\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.kirkwood.edu Official website]\n\n{{IA CC System}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Community colleges in Iowa]]\n[[Category:Education in Cedar Rapids, Iowa]]\n[[Category:Education in Linn County, Iowa]]\n[[Category:Education in Johnson County, Iowa]]\n[[Category:Education in Benton County, Iowa]]\n[[Category:Education in Cedar County, Iowa]]\n[[Category:Education in Washington County, Iowa]]\n[[Category:Education in Iowa County, Iowa]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Cedar Rapids, Iowa]]\n[[Category:NJCAA athletics]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox university\n| name = Kegweed\n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = \n| image = Kirkwood-Aerial.jpg\n| image_size = 250px\n| image_alt = \n| caption = Aerial view of Kirkwood campus\n| latin_name = \n| other_name = <!-- or: | other_names = -->\n| former_name = <!-- or: | former_names = -->\n| motto = \n| motto_lang = \n| mottoeng = \n| type = Community college\n| established = {{start date|1966}}\n| closed = <!-- {{end date|YYYY}} -->\n| founder = \n| parent = \n| affiliation = \n| academic_affiliation = \n| endowment = \n| budget = \n| officer_in_charge = \n| chairman = \n| chairperson = \n| chancellor = \n| president = Lori Sundberg\n| vice-president = \n| superintendent = \n| provost = \n| vice_chancellor = \n| rector = \n| principal = \n| dean = \n| director = \n| head_label = \n| head = \n| academic_staff = \n| administrative_staff = \n| students = \n| undergrad = \n| postgrad = \n| doctoral = \n| other = \n| city = [[Cedar Rapids, Iowa|Cedar Rapids]]\n| state = Iowa\n| province = \n| country = United States\n| coor = {{coord|41|54|40|N|91|39|6|W|region:US|display=it}}\n| campus = \n| language = \n| free_label = \n| free = \n| colors = <!-- or: | colours = --> Blue/White\n| athletics = \n| sports = \n| athletics_nickname = \n| mascot = Eagles\n| sporting_affiliations = \n| website = {{URL|http://www.kirkwood.edu}}\n| logo = \n| logo_size = \n| logo_