ing/index</ref> consist of men's and women's basketball, baseball, softball, volleyball, and men's golf. The college is a member of the [[National Junior College Athletic Association|National Junior College Athletic Association (NJCAA)]], competing in the [[Iowa Community College Athletic Conference|Iowa Community College Athletic Conference (ICCAC)]]. Kirkwood's colors are blue and white, and its mascot is an eagle named \"Sammy\".\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.kirkwood.edu Official website]\n\n{{IA CC System}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Community colleges in Iowa]]\n[[Category:Education in Cedar Rapids, Iowa]]\n[[Category:Education in Linn County, Iowa]]\n[[Category:Education in Johnson County, Iowa]]\n[[Category:Education in Benton County, Iowa]]\n[[Category:Education in Cedar County, Iowa]]\n[[Category:Education in Washington County, Iowa]]\n[[Category:Education in Iowa County, Iowa]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Cedar Rapids, Iowa]]\n[[Category:NJCAA athletics]]\n", "name_user": "Jpate0200", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kirkwood_Community_College"}
